# Test failure diagnosis

When tests fail during development or via [fix_tests.md](../commands/fix_tests.md):

## 1. Collect evidence

- Surefire report: `target/surefire-reports/*.txt`
- Console stack trace from `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=Class#method`

## 2. Classify

| Type | Signs | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| Production bug | Wrong status, missing validation, broken template | Fix `src/main` or templates |
| Test bug | Wrong assertion, stale `App` DSL, wrong `Given` | Fix test |
| Data/setup | Missing seed, wrong `Given`, shared data pollution | Fix test data; call `Given.cleanup()` |
| Environment | Chrome headless, DB, port | Set `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true`; check `%test` config |

## 3. Fix one root cause at a time

- Re-run single test: `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=ClassName#methodName`
- Then class, then profile (`-Ptest-unit`, `-Ptest-web`), then full `verify`

## 4. Report template

After fixing, write `reports/{NNN}-test-failure-{Class}-{method}-{timestamp}.md`:

```markdown
# Test failure report

- **Test:** ClassName#methodName
- **Root cause:** (one sentence)
- **Fix:** (files changed)
- **Verify:** GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=... (pass)
```

## Rules

- Domain spec wins over test expectation when behaviour is specified.
- Never `@Disabled` or `Thread.sleep()` as fixes.
- Never bypass `App` with raw Selenium for HTMX flows.
